post_text:
Solar Eclipse Message:

This is a message from the Hollister School District. On Monday, August 21st, students will be observing the solar eclipse from their classroom or library on a live stream through electronic devices or TV. If you have any questions, please contact your school site. Have a great weekend.

Este es un mensaje del Distrito Escolar de Hollister. El
lunes, 21 de agosto, los estudiantes estarán observando el eclipse solar desde su salon o biblioteca en una transmisión en vivo a través de dispositivos electrónicos o television. Si tiene alguna pregunta, comuníquese con su escuela. Ten un excelente fin de semana.

This is a message from the Hollister School District. On Monday, August 21st, students will be observing the solar eclipse from their classroom or library on a live stream through electronic devices or TV. If you have any questions, please contact your school site. Have a great weekend.

post_text:
The agenda item titled "Delete Board Policy 5127 - Graduation Ceremonies and Activities " on the April 25th, 2017 Board meeting DOES NOT eliminate promotion ceremonies and activities that are held at the end of the each year. This is a Board Policy that is for high schools ONLY that outlines criteria for high school students to graduate high school and participate in high school graduation activities.

Hollister School District will continue to have promotion ceremonies and activities. Thank you for your continued support.

Information from the Board Agenda item # 13.K:

Rationale:
BP 5127 is an optional policy is for use by any district that maintains a high school and is not to be modified to be used in elementary districts. This policy is in conflict with our Board Policy 5123 on promotion, acceleration, and retention of K-8th grade students.

https://hollister.agendaonline.net/public/Meeting.aspx?AgencyID=180&MeetingID=40329&AgencyTypeID=1&IsArchived=False

post_text: The Hollister School District recently received notice that we were approved for a student nutrition program we applied for late last year. This new program will allow us to provide free breakfasts and lunches to all students at Calaveras School, the Accelerated Achievement Academy, Gabilan Hill Elementary School, Hollister Dual Language Academy, R.O. Hardin Elementary School and Sunnylope Elementary School. This program, known as the Community Eligibility Provision of the National School Lunch Program, will provide nutritious meals to each student at those schools, and at Hollister Prep School, regardless of family income.
shared_text:
HESD.ORG
Superintendent's Message • Page - Hollister School District
text:
The Hollister School District recently received notice that we were approved for a student nutrition program we applied for late last year. This new program will allow us to provide free breakfasts and lunches to all students at Calaveras School, the Accelerated Achievement Academy, Gabilan Hill Elementary School, Hollister Dual Language Academy, R.O. Hardin Elementary School and Sunnylope Elementary School. This program, known as the Community Eligibility Provision of the National School Lunch Program, will provide nutritious meals to each student at those schools, and at Hollister Prep School, regardless of family income.

HESD.ORG
Superintendent's Message • Page - Hollister School District

post_text:
Providing FREE LUNCH
for all children who are 18 years and younger
at the following locations:

June 24th 2014-July 30th 2014
R.O. Hardin Elementary School Kitchen
881 Line St
Time: 11:30 AM-12:30 PM

June 24th 2014-July 22nd 2014
Sunnyslope Elementary School Kitchen
1475 Memorial Drive
Time: 11:15 AM-11:45 AM

July 2nd 2014-July 30th 2014
Ladd Lane Elementary School Kitchen
161 Ladd Lane
Time: 11:00 AM-11:30 AM

Sites are open Monday through Friday and will be closed on July 4th.

Important information regarding the program:
1. You do not have to be enrolled in Summer School to be eligible to receive a free meal
2. Meals must be eaten at the site and can not be taken home
3. Adults may purchase meals for $3.00

post_text: The Hollister School District, Hollister, San Benito County, California, hereby gives notice that it is circulating a request for proposal (an “RFP”) to qualified service providers for the Controlled Access Projects within the Hollister School District. The full scope of services and details regarding the District’s Controlled Access Projects is described in more detail in the RFP. Plans and specifications will be available on May 5, 2014 at DLG Printing, located at 435 San Benito Street, Hollister, CA 95023 or (831) 637-3347. The plans and specifications are listed under Hollister School District – Controlled Access Projects. (More info, click on link)
